Change Language Settings for a Cisco Webex Site in Cisco Webex Control Hub
As a site administrator, you can change the language settings for your Webex site to make it more accessible to your users.
Change the Default Language for a Site
You can change the default language of your Webex site, so that users who havenâ€™t set their language preference see the site and meeting invitations in the default language.
1
Sign in to Control Hub, and go to Services > Meeting.
2
Click Sites, choose the Webex site that you want to change the settings for, and then click Settings.
3
Under Common Settings, select Site Options.
4
In the Languages section, choose the default language from the Default language for the Webex site drop-down list.
5
Click Save.
Change the Languages Available to Users
You can choose what languages are available to your users, in case your site does not support certain languages.
1
Sign in to Control Hub, and go to Services > Meeting.
2
Click Sites, choose the Webex site that you want to change the settings for, and then click Settings.
3
Under Common Settings, select Site Options.
4
Go to Languages available in Preferences, and check the check box next to each language you want to make available to users.
5
Click Save.